the cost of accommodation…. it’s very difficult to afford accommodations with the money I’ve saved up….

I’m very concerned and discouraged…. I heard about a number of scams and heard that you need to be vigilant buying sights one rent….

I’m very concerned about this issue.

I just retired and worked VERY HARD to travel all around Europe. I am 80 and now unable to travel and there is one more place I want to go…Jamaica for 3 months. When I first started traveling 2 years ago I went to several scuba diving shops looking into classes because I really wanted to get my certification. I don’t know much, except I like water and I really like swimming, I can barely tread water but I dressed up for scuba diving several times. Needless to say, I didn’t do it but there were many over 70 professions for instructors. Why can I go scuba diving with my arthritis? It is a thrill when you learn you are comfortable breathing underwater and there are many other activities I loved such as windsurfing. Freedom of everything in the Caribbean is gone, especially music. In Jamaica they don’t play RASTA but JAMMIE 92 ROCKS.

I read your story which is impressive. How were you able to launch your business as a senior and not as a young lady? I was also very physically active in my younger life having taught for thirty years and now retired contentedly never giving a second guess at just playing it
